docs/specs/v1-routing-spec.md:1:# v1 Routing Spec — `@relay-assistant/routing`
docs/specs/v1-routing-spec.md:5:**Package:** `@relay-assistant/routing`
docs/specs/v1-routing-spec.md:13:`@relay-assistant/routing` manages model selection and routing-mode decisions across an assistant's coordination context. It is the layer that translates cost/latency/quality requirements into concrete model choices, without knowing about business logic or user-facing content.
docs/specs/v1-routing-spec.md:15:This package is directly informed by Workforce routing patterns: cheap/fast/deep mode tiers, per-request cost envelopes, and quality-preserving routing with configurable thresholds.
docs/specs/v1-routing-spec.md:19:- `ModelSelector` — given a routing context, returns a model specification
docs/specs/v1-routing-spec.md:20:- `RoutingPolicy` — per-assistant and per-capability routing rules; configures when to use each mode
docs/specs/v1-routing-spec.md:23:- Latency envelope — per-request latency target; routing selects models that can meet it
docs/specs/v1-routing-spec.md:27:- The actual model API calls (→ product code or capability handlers; routing provides the model spec, not the invocation)
docs/specs/v1-routing-spec.md:29:- Coordination logic or specialist delegation (→ `@relay-assistant/coordination`)
docs/specs/v1-routing-spec.md:30:- Connectivity signals (→ `@relay-assistant/connectivity`; routing receives escalation signals from connectivity, does not emit them)
docs/specs/v1-routing-spec.md:39:- Routing does not make semantic content decisions. It does not read message text to decide routing; it reads structured context (capability name, cost envelope, escalation signals, constraints).
docs/specs/v1-routing-spec.md:40:- Routing does not define model IDs. It defines `ModelSpec` — a structured description that product code resolves to a concrete model ID. This keeps routing OSS and provider-agnostic.
docs/specs/v1-routing-spec.md:41:- Routing does not enforce policy; it recommends. The caller may override a routing decision if it has product-specific reasons.
