docs/architecture/v1-coordination-implementation-plan.md:21:v1 coordination delivers the **minimal contracts** for one assistant to orchestrate multiple internal specialists and synthesize a single coherent response. The scope is:
docs/architecture/v1-coordination-implementation-plan.md:27:5. **Connectivity integration** — the coordinator listens for connectivity signals from specialists and uses them to make coordination decisions (handoffs, escalations, conflicts)
docs/architecture/v1-coordination-implementation-plan.md:34:- **No routing integration.** Coordination does not select models or response modes. It may receive routing-mode suggestions via connectivity escalation signals, but it does not call the routing package directly.
docs/architecture/v1-coordination-implementation-plan.md:37:- **No persistent delegation state.** Delegation plans and specialist results are in-memory for the duration of one coordination turn. No storage backend is required.
docs/architecture/v1-coordination-implementation-plan.md:43:All files are created under `packages/coordination/`.
docs/architecture/v1-coordination-implementation-plan.md:119:  status: 'complete' | 'partial' | 'failed';
