docs/architecture/traits-and-persona-layer.md:29:A routing profile selects which persona tier to use per intent. The workload-router resolves `intent → persona + tier → concrete runtime config`. Personas are defined in and owned by Workforce infrastructure. They are not imported into this SDK.
docs/architecture/traits-and-persona-layer.md:69:SDK routing modes (`cheap`/`fast`/`deep`) are SDK vocabulary for latency/depth/cost decisions. Workforce uses `minimum`/`best-value`/`best` for tier names. The mapping is intentional and explicit — products map between them. Neither package should adopt the other's naming.
