docs/architecture/v1-coordination-routing-integration-review-verdict.md:29:### 1. Does coordination now consume routing in a clean, bounded way?
docs/architecture/v1-coordination-routing-integration-review-verdict.md:33:The integration satisfies the plan's design principle that coordination accepts a router but never creates one:
docs/architecture/v1-coordination-routing-integration-review-verdict.md:35:- `package.json` lists `@relay-assistant/routing` as a **devDependency**, not a runtime dependency. ✓
docs/architecture/v1-coordination-routing-integration-review-verdict.md:36:- `coordination/src/types.ts` line 5 uses `import type { RequestedRoutingMode, RoutingMode }` — type-only imports erased at compile time, zero runtime coupling. ✓
docs/architecture/v1-coordination-routing-integration-review-verdict.md:37:- `CoordinationRouter` is a **structural interface** (plan §2), not a direct import of `Router`. A real `Router` from `@relay-assistant/routing` satisfies it structurally without an adapter. ✓
docs/architecture/v1-coordination-routing-integration-review-verdict.md:39:- The coordinator calls `router.decide()` before each step (coordination.ts lines 326–349) and `router.recordCost()` after steps with cost metadata (lines 365–367). It does not interpret the returned mode, forward it anywhere other than `SpecialistContext`, or hold any routing policy. ✓
docs/architecture/v1-coordination-routing-integration-review-verdict.md:40:- `SpecialistContext.routingDecision` and `CoordinationTurn.routingDecisions` are plain value objects, not routing types. The coordinator copies out the fields it needs and discards the `Router` type surface. ✓
docs/architecture/v1-coordination-routing-integration-review-verdict.md:42:**One minor deviation from plan:** `coordination/src/types.ts` imports both `RoutingMode` and `RequestedRoutingMode` from routing (plan §2 mentioned importing only `RoutingMode`). Since `RequestedRoutingMode = RoutingMode` (an exact alias at `routing/src/types.ts` line 68), this is harmless but adds one more type name to the dependency surface than planned. Both are erased at runtime.
docs/architecture/v1-coordination-routing-integration-review-verdict.md:48:**PASS — both F-3 and F-4 from the routing review are fully resolved**
